flowRoot.flowPara: Here is the laser source. For simplicity, it is a non-tuneable HeNe laser at a 632nm wavelength for simplicity
mirrors to redirect the beam towards the sample and detector
(if the beam is resonant with a transition)
The detector measures the beams power and sends out a continuous analog signal, typically in Volts.
The computer then collects the raw data into a file for processing.
The analog signals is converted into a digital signal so that it maybe be passed on to a computer.
This is a beam splitter. It splits the beam so that a part of the laser beam can be measured
attenuation and or filtering of the beam for desirable properties
Some modification to the input HeNe Laser
If you really want to be fancy, you can process the data during collection
